  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dca\u0da2\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0ddd  \u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf \u0db1\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dc4\u0dc3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ranjan is free tomorrow or Monday",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Harin Fernando says that former Member of Parliament Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake, who has been convicted under charges of contempt of court, will be released tomorrow or next Monday.",
        "He mentions this in a statement on his Twitter account. Mr. Hareen Fernando said on his Twitter account that he and Minister Manusha Nanayakkara and a number of other parties have requested the President Ranil Wickramasinghe to release Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake.",
        "The Minister also said that he would like to thank Minister Vijayadasa Rajapaksa for his support in releasing Mr. Ranjan Ramanayake."
      ],
